{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/pulls/378", "id": 545833470, "node_id": "MDExOlB1bGxSZXF1ZXN0NTQ1ODMzNDcw", "html_url": "https://github.com/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/pull/378", "diff_url": "https://github.com/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/pull/378.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/pull/378.patch", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/issues/378", "number": 378, "state": "closed", "locked": false, "title": "Switch Text Shaping to rustybuzz", "user": {"login": "CryZe", "id": 1451630, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjE0NTE2MzA=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1451630?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe", "html_url": "https://github.com/CryZe", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/CryZe/received_events", "type": "User", "user_view_type": "public", "site_admin": false}, "body": "rustybuzz is a more or less complete port of harfbuzz (state of the art) text shaping engine to Rust. This means our font handling is now about as good as the one found in a browser, except all the manual things you may need to do on top such as using different fonts for different parts of the text, because some glyphs are not available in the chosen font and handling image based glyphs such as those that are being used for emojis in some fonts. Overall though switching to rustybuzz seems to have already changed the appearance quite a bit. There is now proper kerning (though I thought rusttype already did that, but apparently not), proper ligature support and because this is state of the art, it also supports tabular numbers for example which is now activated for all the numbers that we are rendering. Unfortunately since rustybuzz does so much more work, it also heavily slowed down text shaping, which we do on every frame at the moment. So we really need to refactor the renderer to start caching a lot more stuff.", "created_at": "2020-12-27T17:10:29Z", "updated_at": "2021-11-16T20:20:23Z", "closed_at": "2020-12-27T18:19:21Z", "merged_at": "2020-12-27T18:19:21Z", "merge_commit_sha": "2391a089c37b513134d6ab1a439caf370e304a2d", "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "requested_reviewers": [], "requested_teams": [], "labels": [{"id": 506643205, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw1MDY2NDMyMDU=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/labels/enhancement", "name": "enhancement", "color": "84b6eb", "default": true, "description": "An improvement for livesplit-core."}, {"id": 1274202234, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMjc0MjAyMjM0", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/labels/rendering", "name": "rendering", "color": "edcf5a", "default": false, "description": "The issue or pull request is affecting the rendering."}, {"id": 1319882119, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMzE5ODgyMTE5", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/labels/feature", "name": "feature", "color": "8ec633", "default": false, "description": "A new user visible feature for livesplit-core."}, {"id": 2103077489, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTAzMDc3NDg5", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/labels/performance", "name": "performance", "color": "ef957f", "default": false, "description": "Affects the performance of the code."}], "milestone": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/LiveSplit/livesplit-core/milestones/4", "html_url": "https://github.com/LiveSplit/liv